### 3.4 Authentication & Security

| Technology | Version | Role |
|---|---|---|
| **JWT (`jsonwebtoken`)** | v9.0.3 | Stateless token auth for both users and admins |
| **`bcryptjs`** | v3.0.3 | Secure password hashing before DB storage |
| **`cookie-parser`** | v1.4.7 | Cookie-based token reading/writing |
| **`cors`** | v2.8.6 | Cross-origin request handling (credentials: true) |

**Auth Flow:**
1. User registers → password hashed via bcrypt → stored in Supabase
2. Login → JWT issued → stored in HttpOnly cookie
3. Protected routes → `requireUser` middleware validates JWT
4. Admin panel → separate password + `ADMIN_JWT_SECRET`

