### 3.8 DevOps & Deployment

| Technology | Role |
|---|---|
| **Vercel** | Cloud hosting & CI/CD deployment |
| **`@vercel/node`** | Serverless Node.js runtime on Vercel |
| **`vercel.json`** | Deployment config — all routes proxied through `server.js` |
| **GitHub** | Source control & version management |
| **`.env` / `.env.example`** | Local secrets management |
| **`start.bat`** | Windows convenience script for local dev startup |

**Vercel Configuration:**
```json
{
  "builds": [{ "src": "server.js", "use": "@vercel/node" }],
  "routes": [{ "src": "/(.*)", "dest": "server.js" }]
}
```
> All traffic (including static files) is routed through `server.js`, which serves the `/public` directory via `express.static`.

